radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver shows homogenous attenuation without focal lesions or biliary dilatation. The pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands are normal. Kidneys are symmetric with no focal lesions or hydronephrosis. The appendix is air-filled proximally but fluid-filled and dilated distally. There is trace free fluid in the pelvis. An intrauterine device is malpositioned and a left corpus luteal cyst is noted. No lymphadenopathy or vascular issues detected. No acute fractures.
